header.gameNote: PARADISE JAM AT ST JOHN VIRGIN ISLANDS

article.headline: Fordham 72, Norfolk State 53
article.story: CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Marcus Stout scored 21 points to lead Fordham to a 72-53 victory over Norfolk State at the Paradise Jam tournament on Monday. Bryant Dunston had 15 points and Michael Binns added 14 points for Fordham, which finished fifth in the six-team round-robin tournament. The lead changed six times in the first period before Fordham pulled away, finishing the half with a 38-27 lead. The Spartans never lead in the second half. Tony Murphy had 13 points and Calvin Brown had 12 points and eight rebounds for Norfolk State, which finished a winless sixth.
